ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Office Excel Chart Object Memory Corruption

EngDesc.value:
A code execution vulnerability exists in Microsoft Office Excel. The vulnerability is due to the way the vulnerable product parses Excel documents, allowing for memory corruption. Remote attackers can exploit this vulnerability by enticing target users to open a malicious Excel file, potentially causing arbitrary code to be injected and executed in the security context of the current logged on user.
In an attack scenario, where arbitrary code is injected and executed on the target machine, the behaviour of the target is dependent on the intention of the malicious code. If such an attack is not executed successfully, the vulnerable application may terminate abnormally.
